"Horiuchi K., Gol'dberg E.L., Matsuzaki H., Kobayashi K., Shibata Y.","Verification of magnetostratigraphic scales of miocene core section from lake Baikal",2004,"Geologiya i Geofizika","45","3",,"408","412",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-2942565826&partnerID=40&md5=c2db935e1c756707be81df1a660cf61a",,"Horiuchi, K.; Gol'dberg, E.L.; Matsuzaki, H.; Kobayashi, K.; Shibata, Y.","The dynamics of cosmogenic 10Be contents in the BDP-96-1 (100 to 200 m) and BDP-98-2 (200 to 600 m) cores was used to test published magnetostratigraphic scales for the Miocene section and to time the core base. Only one of three alternative scales for the BDP-98 core tested against the 10Be decay of T1/2 = 1.5 myr showed a perfect consistency with the decay law. The basal age of the 600 m BDP-98 section was estimted at 8.4 myr.","Cosmogenic10Be; Global climate change; Lake Baikal; Magnetostratigraphy; Miocene; Paleoclimate","cosmogenic radionuclide; magnetostratigraphy; Miocene; Eurasia; Lake Baikal; Russian Federation",,,,,,"(2000), 41 (1), pp. 3-32. , Russian source. T. cAntipin, V., Afonina, T., Badalov, O., The new BDP-98 600-m drill core from Lake Baikal: A key late Cenozoic sedimentary section in continental Asia (2001) Quat. Int., 80-81, pp. 19-36; Kashiwaya, K., Ochiai, S., Sakai, H., Kawai, T., Orbit-related long-term climate cycles revealed in a 12-Myr continental record from Lake Baikal (2001) Nature, 410, pp. 71-74; Kashiwaya, K., Ochiai, S., Tsukahara, H., Some issues to be considered in establishing age models for the long Lake Baikal sediments records (2002) Quat. Int., 95-96, pp. 205-207; Prokopenko, A.A., Karabanov, E.B., Williams, D., Age of long sediment core from Lake Baikal (2002) Nature, 415, p. 976. , (comments); Kashiwaya, K., Ochiachi, S., Sakai, H., Kawai, T., Age of long sediment core from Lake Baikal (2002) Nature, 415, p. 976. , (replay); Sakai, H., Nomura, S., Horii, M., Paleomagnetism and paleo-environmental magnetism studied on BDP-98 sedi